There is wear primarily on the inside corners where they rubbed while in the holster, but there is also much evidence externally of it being a true "on the job" weapon. Bore and chambers on the cylinder are good and have been well maintained. After all, this officer's life depended on this gun working every time he might have to pull the trigger.The gun came to me with beautiful custom-made dark walnut with target thumb rest grips.
